channel.description: The latest CVEs for IBM -- Partner Engagement Manager

item.title: CVE-2022-34348|2024-08-03T09:07:16.149Z -- ibm -- partner%20engagement%20manager
item.description: IBM Sterling Partner Engagement Manager 6.1 is vulnerable to an XML External Entity Injection (XXE) attack when processing XML data. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to expose sensitive information or consume memory resources. IBM X-Force ID: 230017.

item.title: CVE-2022-34354|2024-08-03T09:07:16.140Z -- ibm -- partner%20engagement%20manager
item.description: IBM Sterling Partner Engagement Manager 2.0 allows encrypted storage of client data to be stored locally which can be read by another user on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 230424.
